<HEAD>
<TITLE> Accession to the Geneva Conventions by the Republic of Lithuania </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<P>
<P>
<P>
<TABLE>
<TR valign=top><TD>
<P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/IconICRC.gif" ALIGN=left HSPACE=10></TD><TD>
<P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/ButtonBar.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#ButtonBar"><MAP NAME="ButtonBar"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="0,0,117,19" HREF="/index.htm"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="121,0,238,19" HREF="/icrcnews/neuf.htm" ALT="What's news"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="241,0,358,19" HREF="http://gvalnex1.icrc.org/icrcnews/search.htm" ALT="Search page"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="358,0,475,19" HREF="/icrcnews/SiteTree.htm" ALT="Site tree"></MAP><BR>

<P><B>16 December 1996</B>
<P>
<P><B>International Review of the Red Cross</B>  <B>no 314, p.569</B><BR>
</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/Separator_Line_ICRC.gif" BORDER=0><BR>

<P>
<P>
<H2>Accession to the Geneva Conventions by the Republic of Lithuania </H2>
<P><I></I>
<P>
<P>The Republic of Lithuania acceded on 3 October 1996, without making any declaration or reservations, to the Geneva Conventions of 12 August 1949. <BR>

<P>Pursuant to their provisions, the Conventions will come into force for the Republic of Lithuania on 3 April 1997. <BR>

<P>This accession brings to <B>188</B> the number of States party to the Geneva Conventions. <BR>

