<HTML> 
<HEAD>
<TITLE> An end to isolation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<P>
<P>
<P>
<TABLE>
<TR valign=top><TD>
<P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/IconICRC.gif" ALIGN=left HSPACE=10></TD><TD>
<P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/ButtonBar.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#ButtonBar"><MAP NAME="ButtonBar"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="0,0,117,19" HREF="/index.htm"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="121,0,238,19" HREF="/icrcnews/neuf.htm" ALT="What's news"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="241,0,358,19" HREF="http://gvalnex1.icrc.org/icrcnews/search.htm" ALT="Search page"><AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="358,0,475,19" HREF="/icrcnews/SiteTree.htm" ALT="Site tree"></MAP><BR>

<P><B>26 March 1996</B>
<P>
<P><B>Extract from  &quot;Saving lives&quot;</B>  <B></B><BR>
</TD></TR></TABLE>

<P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/Separator_Line_ICRC.gif" BORDER=0><BR>

<P>
<P>
<H2>An end to isolation</H2>
<P><I></I>
<P>
<P>
<H4><B>The Tracing Agency's role in protection</B></H4>
<P>
<P>Nearly four million civilians have been displaced since the outbreak of fighting in the former Yugoslavia, the largest population movement in Europe for the past 50 years. Countless families have been split up, children have lost their parents, family members have been incarcerated, and many have died. The destruction of the family unit, compounded by the breakdown of communications resulting from the conflict, has led to widespread and profound feelings of insecurity and vulnerability.<BR>

<P>
<H4><B>Anxious for news</B></H4>
<P>
<P>To alleviate the distress of people who are without news of their relatives, the ICRC has launched one of the most extensive operations for tracing missing persons and restoring family links in its history.<BR>

<P>The Red Cross message network forwarded more than 11 million messages across front lines and borders in 1994. Hundreds of people are involved in this task including more than 100 National Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies as well as ICRC delegates and local staff and local Red Cross volunteers in the former Yugoslavia. Thanks to the Red Cross, hundreds of thousands of families have been able to trace their relatives.<BR>

<P>
<P><IMG src="258a_0.gif"> Feric/ICRC<BR>
<I>Between 1992 and 1994 some 275,000 Red Cross messages maintained a link specifically<BR>
between detainees and their families.</I><BR>

<P>Once contact is restored, the ICRC arranges family reunifications across front lines. Owing to the enormity of the task, priority is given to the most vulnerable, i.e. children, the elderly and women, in the belief that this is the best way of ensuring their protection. More than 5,000 people have been reunited with relatives since 1992.<BR>

<P>By means of its visits to detainees, the ICRC has been able to locate thousands of prisoners and end their isolation by putting them in touch with their families through Red Cross messages. All detainees seen are registered and monitored throughout their detention in order to prevent disappearances.<BR>

<P>A sophisticated computer programme is used to record details on every individual, together with any further action taken in each case. The database for the former Yugoslavia contains 64,000 names and some 300,000 items of information for passing on to families.<BR>

<P>Despite all these efforts, many families are still without news of relatives who have been missing for months or more. The ICRC acts as an intermediary between these families and the warring parties, approaching the various authorities concerned in order to determine the whereabouts of missing persons. The operation's success obviously depends on the willingness of the authorities to provide the ICRC and the families with replies.<BR>

<P>
<P><IMG src="258a_1.gif">
<P><I>Thank you for the lights you brought us</I><BR>
<I>Thank you for the support to hold on</I><BR>
<I>Thank you for the human words</I><BR>
<I>Thank you for gifts</I><BR>
<I>Thanks to Caroline, Jean and everybody else</I><BR>

<P><A HREF="367a.htm">Previous page</A><BR>
<A HREF="3eba.htm">Table of contents</A></P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/Separator_Line_ICRC.gif" BORDER=0><P><IMG SRC="/gifsICRC/ButtonBar.gif" BORDER=0 USEMAP="#ButtonBar"><BR>

<P>
<P>
</BODY>
