<P>8. See, for instance, Article 3 of the Swiss <I>Arr&ecirc;t&eacute; f&eacute;d&eacute;ral</I> &quot;<I>concernant la Croix-Rouge suisse</I>&quot; of 13 June 1951, which grants both financial support and fiscal exemptions to the Red Cross Society.  The <I>Arr&ecirc;t&eacute; f&eacute;d&eacute;ral</I> takes into account the unique position of the National Society within the country: &quot;<I>La Conf&eacute;d&eacute;ration tient compte de la situation particuti&egrave;re de la Croix-Rouge en lui garantissant un appui financier ainsi que des facilit&eacute;s sp&eacute;ciales.  La Conf&eacute;d&eacute;ration accorde chaque ann&eacute;e &agrave; la Croix-Rouge suisse: a) une subvention pour I'accomplissement des t&acirc;ches mentionn&eacute;es &agrave; I'article 2; b) une subvention sp&eacute;ciale pour former et tenir &agrave; disposition un personnel infirmier professionnel en vue de I'aide sanitaire volontaire.  Le montant de ces subventions sera fix&eacute; dans le budget. Les facilit&eacute;s qui peuvent &ecirc;tre accord&eacute;es &agrave; la Croix-Rouge suisse concernent en particulier I'exemption partielle ou compl&egrave;te de taxes, &eacute;moluments et imp&ocirc;ts, en tant que les dispositions l&eacute;gales le permettent.</I>&quot;<BR>

<P>9. See, Article 20 of the German Constitution (<I>Grundgesetz</I>), which states the social welfare principle.  Pursuant to this principle, the government has to support all non-governmental organizations, such as the German Red Cross, that conduct welfare activities.  Accordingly, the German Red Cross receives an annual grant from the government.<BR>

<P>10. A similar reasoning has been upheld by the United States Supreme Court in <I>Department of Employment v. United States</I> (see below, p. 465).<BR>

<P>11. In May 1996.<BR>

<P>12. At that time the red cross was not yet the official symbol, and what were to become Red Cross or Red Crescent Societies were called &quot;Relief Committees&quot;.<BR>

<P>13. Resolution of 21 September 1946 (document E/232).<BR>

