<P>23.   The Group of Three, established by the Convention against Apartheid is an <I>ad hoc</I> body and meets only once every 2 years. The problem with such an <I>ad hoc</I> group is that between meetings there is no body to take any action. This has become painfully obvious during the recent elections in South Africa, when the body could not convene, because at that time the Group of Three did not have any members.<BR>

